
# Overview

This report is about BrightTV subscription data analyses. The data was collected over a period of three months (Q1).
Bright TV ‘s CEO has an objective to grow the company’s subscription base for this financial year. He has approached me to provide 
insights that would assist CVM (Customer Value Management) team in meeting this year’s objective. The dataset was also provided which 
contained information about user profiles and viewer transactions for Bright TV.
My task is to  prepare a 20 min presentation that will cover the following topics:
# Objectives
Insights on user and usage trends of BrightTV. 
What type of factors influence consumption? 
What content would I recommend in increasing consumption on the days with low consumption? 
What type of initiatives would I recommend to further grow bright TV ‘s User base. The  
Times and dates given in the dataset are supplied in UTC and expected to be converted to SA time.
Following the above instruction, I embarked on the journey to execute the analysis.

Miro was used to map the data flow, from source to storage, including ETL processes, key calculations, 
and insights, providing a clear visual blueprint of the data pipeline and analytics plan.
Data Processing as Summarised:
Received Excel data, converted to CSV, and loaded into Databricks. 
Performed data cleaning and transformations, including correcting entries and computing total amounts. 
Created 8 new tables from the transformed data. 
Used SQL to aggregate data by Age group, day classification, day name, time bucket etc.

Exported transformed data back to Excel. 
Generated pivot tables for subscription analysis
Minute by Time of day
Duration by Gender
Duration by Province
Duration by Race
Duration Day Name
