Insights:
Gauteng, Western Cape, and Kwa-Zulu Natal, drives 66% of minute analyzed
Young Adults and  Adults contribute 93% of viewership
While males dominate at 88%, senior, elderly, and unknown gender
remain underrepresented, presenting a clear opportunity for growth

What they watch?
Insights: 
48% Sport contributes 43.5K of minutes,
ICC Cricket and  Super Sport

25%  Music and lifestyle
 Channel 0 and Trace TV
 Youth is booming 

9% Kids - Boomerang and cartoon Network- family matters
The 20% shared is open for growth

What factor drives or limits consumption for Bright TV
Insights:

Five factors found to drive or limit consumption

Channels: Sport carries the platform by 48%,
ICC Cricket and SuperSport. Content concentration at risk
Saturday is peak — Monday inactive.

2.  Young Adults and Adults peak at ~18K on Saturday.      
Monday drops to ~7.5K — a clear scheduling gap to fill

3. Day-part, Evening strong, mornings abandoned
Male prime-time evening dominates at 30K+. Morning and afternoon slots are almost empty —
seniors and children have nothing to watch.

4. Regions: Gauteng does all the heavy lifting
GP at ~23K, WC at ~11K. Limpopo, Northern Cape, Northwest under 3K each
— rural audiences are not being reached.

5. Demographics: Age 50+ and children are invisible
Young Adults and Adults dominate every chart. Seniors (04) barely register.
Children (01) underserved despite weekend availability. Female viewership very 
low across all time slots.

CVM Team Growth Initiatives  
Females dominate 9.1% of viewership
Develop bundle for Lifestyle, drama & wellness pack to close the 88/12 male skew. Targeted in-app trial + WhatsApp onboarding.
Plan Family & Kids contents
Only 9% of  channel market is served. Bundle Boomerang + Cartoon + family movies. 
Promote weekend mornings — currently empty inventory

Sport Memberships 
Sports events are Seasonal convert events in annual subscriptions.
Tap into Regional Development Concentrate content local partners in Limpopo, Free State and Eastern Cape 

Senior group 50+ plan
Nearly, invisible audience nonetheless significant to make present every day.
News (CNN) + classic movies + simplified UI. A nearly empty segment with high LTV potential

Recommndations 
Monday is the weakest day across every time bucket. 
New content prioritised for Monday to boost weekend comeback.
Wednesday and Thursday are rivals for Friday afternoon. 
The mid-week content can boost sustainability throughout the week.
Boost the morning slot programme for the second reliable viewing peak
Although Night & Graveyard slots have minimal viewership, they are present every day.

Tools and Technologies
Databricks: Data storage, transformation, and SQL analysis
Excel: Pivot tables, charts, and visual analysis
PowerPoint: CEO presentation
Miro: Data flow and architecture planning
Daily Performance dashboard 
The dashboard was designed using Microsoft Excel to ensure clarity and usability. 
Key performance indicators (KPIs) are displayed using charts and summary cards, 
allowing stakeholders to view daily performance. The visual elements included bar charts, line graphs, and pie charts. 
This was used to enhance the ability to identify trends, customer behavioural patterns, and product performance.

Dashboard Key Performance Indicators:
Total Revenue per product category
Viewership by Province
Viewership by Race
Viewership by Gender
Viewership by age group etc
These are trends used for analyses:
Line chart → Viewership minutes by time of day 
Bar chart →  Viewership by category
Pie chart → split by Gender and Province
KPI cards → Total Count, Total Minutes(hours) and Sessions












